      "text": "I wish to discuss the space in which we record symbols. The central idea is that mathematical operations are more clearly expressed in a space which imposes fewer constraints upon the tokens it contains. Tokens placed in lines encourage sequential metaphors, while tokens spread over a plane encourage parallel metaphors. A simple space of representation frees objects within it from irrelevent syntactic constraints."
